message.content:
cs.DC, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is motivated by distributed schedulers and large-scale homogeneous clusters. 
- cs.NE (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses server selection policies and their impact on response time. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper studies the performance of a system with a particular server selection policy. 
- cs.PF (Probability) is relevant as the paper proposes a partial integro-differential equation to describe the evolution of the system and studies the convergence of a fixed point iteration. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper considers general service time distributions and proposes a closed form expression for the limiting response time distribution in case of first-come-first-served scheduling.
